==English==
===Etymology===
{{nautical}} a square-rigged ship is taken aback when the wind blows on the front of the sails

===Verb===
'''to [[take]] [[aback]]'''
#To [[surprise]] or [[shock]]; to [[discomfit]].
#''(nautical) (usually passive)'' Of a ship: to catch it with the sails aback suddenly.

